<p>A similar characterization can also be made using <a href="/wiki/Bramble_(graph_theory)" title="Bramble (graph theory)">brambles</a>, families of connected subgraphs that all touch each other (meaning either that they share a vertex or are connected by an edge).<sup id="cite&#95;ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>4<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> The order of a bramble is the smallest <a href="/wiki/Hitting_set" class="mw-redirect" title="Hitting set">hitting set</a> for the family of subgraphs, and the treewidth of a graph is one less than the maximum order of a bramble.
</p>
